social_posts.post_text:
A little bit here and a little bit over there..daily. My holiday mantra 🎨 
I am always amazed at how the little bits all add up. 
I hope you are finding the time to get your creative ya yas out.
Wishing you all the happy + healthy holiday feels (plus a whole lotta creativity)⭐️May a bright light shine wherever this finds you xx

Wouldn’t it be great if we could just bottle up all of our enthusiasm for the new year? Your new chapter -> so many possibilities all awaiting just for you. 

Thanks for all of the love, encouragement and support around here this year. Always grateful for my “insta-office” 

Paint on my friends💫
Happy to report that there is a whole lotta YES going on over here. Thankful for green painters tape for keeping it all together.

The Art 2 Life Workshop is back again for 2023! Mark your calendars for Mon Feb 13th! It’s free and a perfect opportunity to get a glimpse into the Art 2 Life World.

Every year, Nicholas Wilton and his team offer a free, in depth workshop that gives you a wonderful glimpse into their Art 2 Life program - The Creative Visionary Program.

I am always in awe of the depth of knowledge and experience shared by Nick and his team. They are extremely generous and there is no shortage of interaction, visuals, color mixing, image adjustments and laughs. Lots of fun and a lot of “Do you get it” You will most definitely walk away “Getting it 🎨 You will walk away each day with a new found enthusiasm to play and explore, gaining confidence in your materials and most importantly, in yourself.

No formal art training required. I wish I had been introduced to this program right from the very beginning of my art life. Message me with any questions!

✨Sign up above! Link is in my profile✨

Botanical bits + bops

All the shapes + sizes, oddly drooping or standing up tall, dead or alive….I will take them every which way 🌿

Enjoy the weekend everyone!

Ahhh the mixed emotions of yet another 100 day project. I am feeling perfectly uneasy, excited, overwhelmed and inspired 🙂🙃but it has become a part of who I am and what I do so there is no way I would miss it💫It’s my inspiration and helps generate so many ideas for the year ahead. I hope it inspires you too! 
Onwards-> Year 8! 
Sharing a little glimpse into last years project. The beginning of my journey into bookbinding and the making of books. 
Hands up if you are joining in this year? 🙌 @dothe100dayproject
I have a blog post up with some tips + tricks if you are interested. (link to my Journal is above in my profile)

Paper cut illustrations, collage, painting, mark making, textile art, bookbinding ->
Keeping my head, heart + hands in creative mode. Trying new things, exploring ideas and always learning. This is what gets me excited to get out of bed each morning (and often keeps me up most of the night as well) 

I know there is Something out there that is getting you excited so please just sit down and start. You don’t have to have it all figured out to move forward because A little each day adds up to a lot. Follow each and every idea and before you know it you have got yourself a project. This is your 100 day project.

The @dothe100dayproject community starts tomorrow. You will find more information there and above in my Journal ( in links) with tips + tricks on doing the project. Please sign up for my newsletter to follow along💫

100 DAY PROJECT
Finding my groove as I  settle into another 100 days of daily art. This time around I will be focusing on the making of books and bookbinding. I will be exploring different types of mixed media paper combined with a little mark making, collage, sewing and hopefully a whole lot of surprises along the way as my brain kicks into crazy creative mode 🤞🏻
First up -> Concertina sketchbook
The @dothe10dayproject community is in full swing. Check out #dothe100dayproject so many creative ideas are brewing over there.. For more information + tips + tricks about the project follow the Journal link above in my profile

100 DAY PROJECT

Well, I knew I wouldn’t be able to stop at just one -> landscape inspired concertina sketchbook. I love the unexpected twists + turns that these little sketchbook pages fold up into #dothe100dayproject

100 DAY PROJECT

Where ideas come from-> inspired by my concertina sketchbooks. Colors,shape and line. Feels fresh  to me 💚I am not sure what will become of these, but I was in the flow and you never want to mess with that. 
One week into the project and I hope everyone participating is settling in and feeling good #dothe100dayproject

Bold marks, meandering lines,liminal uncertainty…my brain on vacation 🌊 

All inspired by my landscape concertina sketchbook and places I want to go

My brain on the 100 Day Project. Day 14

A mood board of sorts

I have dusted off my dads old Kenmore, stacked some papers and painted others. I have just started sewing pieces of material together and shuffling things about because I feel that this is going to be an intuitive process for me.It will all come together if I just trust the process. 

#dothe100dayproject

🎨📃 🧵 🪡 
Brushstrokes on canvas and signatures in the making. 
Enjoy the week!
#dothe100dayproject

A mark making lollapalooza
-> More covers because I had to have one in pink and some warm up sheets that will be used for collage fodder within. My goal was to have at least one book finished by the quarter way mark and Surprise Surprise...I think it just might happen🤹‍♀️

#dothe100dayproject

A bit of stitching and soaking and all is coming up Pink around here #dothe100dayproject 

A few blogposts are brewing and coming soon. Please sign up for my newsletter (above in profile) for more 📖

..And another one 📖 
I love watching these books spring into being and their story has just begun. So much more to come #the100dayproject

Enjoying the little details that can easily be done daily. I may not have the time this year to dedicate to my practice, but I know that I can find time daily to slow down, think and be creative. That’s just enough to feed the soul #dothe100dayproject

On my desk today-> All the little bits gathered up from the last month. Pieces of time caught on planes and trains. Some sewing while sitting bedside during hospital visits. Rainy day painting and mindful pattern making during some quiet island. Every piece has its own little story. Unique and handcrafted. These books have definitely become part of my wider art practice💛#the100dayproject
Feeling springlike and very soggy🌱Morning pages inspired by a walk in the woods this weekend.

In and around my studio this week

In my hands —> On my wall —> In my head —> On my desk

The doors are open and the sun is shining in.There really is nothing better than a change in season. Don’t you agree? It has most definitely added a bit of spring to my step. 

Hands up if you are feeling it too ☀️

I know this is long but I just wish it could go on forever…
A little taste of summer here for you!

Morning pages inspired by blue skies and my garden blooms all starting to pop🌺

Structured vs Unstructured

It is still that messy space in between that intrigues me the most. The sense of freedom, the possibility, the great discoveries..both good and bad. It’s where Nothing matters and It’s where all the best stuff happens. Kind of like Life, right? 

Enjoy the week!

100 days + of making books and onwards I go. 

I fell in love with this process and the results just keep getting better. A little unique and definitely handcrafted. I have to admit I do like it all a little rough around the edges- perfectly uneven, crooked stitching, ripped pages and always a smudge or two …the whole process wrapped up nicely into its own little story. 

This has definitely become a part of my wider art practice. More to come!
#the100dayproject

In amongst the great mess of paper I call my studio, my little concertina sketchbook was shouting out loud. Small ideas just wanting a bit of attention. This is what they had to say ->>>

It makes me happy when my sketchbook work grabs my energy and focus and informs my work🎨 Small ideas getting bigger - mixed media on 11x15 watercolor paper

Notes to self…

These always make me laugh as I have such great intentions to follow their guidance. When the brushes start swinging and the paint is flowing Everything is fair game. Sound familiar? 

Spot the daisies->

Inspiration courtesy of this months Fodder School teacher Megan Quinlan. A big thank you for inspiring me to get out the watercolors and practice my patience and perseverance.I loved rediscovering their unpredictable nature and it was easy to just keep on thinking “ what if..” Those are the best kind of days.

I am curious to see where my stepping stones lead me -> Definitely something landscaped inspired. A book for sure and maybe, just maybe,I may try my hand at one of those round canvas. Lots of ideas swirling around 💫 

@meganquinlanstudio @fodder.school 

If you are interested, the ( FREE ) Fodder Challenge starts this Monday. Twelve days + 12 different lessons. All information and sign up is over at @fodder.school 
A perfect summertime activity. 

Enjoy the weekend🎨

A mix + mingle between pieces and the shape of things to come -> Layers, texture, cut outs and lovely watercolor

I love watching where ideas take you, especially within a community setting. So much inspiration + enthusiasm all supplied by this months instructor @meganquinlanstudio and the @fodder.school community 💫 Enjoy the week everyone!

“Out of these small, flat,rigid squares of paper unfolds world after world. Worlds that sing to you, comfort and excite you” Anne Lamott

Another book in the making..

Nooks + crannies, textured paper, cut outs, hits of inspiration and lots of blank pages left for the story to unfold

This months exploration with @fodder.school + @meganquinlanstudio continues💫

“Every new beginning comes from some other beginnings end.. “

Some of my favorite pieces from this month. Earthy, layered, watercolor shapes combined with all the blues and greens of life on the coast -> Sharing a little feel of the seasons of Brunswick Beach with you. These are definitely the beginning of something new.. 

Another enjoyable, educational and always enlightening, month from Julys instructor @meganquinlanstudio + the @fodder.school crew

Morning Pages -> Morning Master Sheets.

Just getting started, but I already know these are going to become one of my things. Some days it’s just too much to break out the paints. Some days you just need to use what you already have. Some days just need to be about the scraps ✂️ 

Fodder School brings us @ricki_ticki_tavy this month and she has very kindly given us permission to use all of the scraps. @fodder.school

Naturally abstract + a bit of mix and mingling between my two loves - free flowing painterly marks + some paper collage botanicals. 

All three paintings are available today in the online “ Naturally Abstracted” Square Foot Show featuring Lori Siebert and friends. It starts today at 5 pm Pacific/8pm Eastern time and runs through the weekend. @lorisiebert.studio @squarefootshow 

Head over to @squarefootshow to browse 50 artists and 250 pieces of one-of-a-kind abstract artwork, all 12”x12”, all $300 ($230US) 

There will be a little bit of something for everyone. I have placed a link to the Show above.

Sitting by the seaside sewing scrappy snippets in the sun☀️ 

I am not sure I have made a dent in my scrap pile yet, but I am definitely enjoying sifting through them all , remembering and rediscovering. I have to laugh though because the scraps of the scraps are now getting their own pile. Does this ever end?

Trying very hard to stop at just one ✂️@ricki_ticki_tavy ->All of your scrap projects are very fun! #fodderschoolproject @fodder.school

When you change the way you look at things, the things you look at change

Snippets + Tags, Master Sheets + Clusters…a whole mouthful of new terminology for me as I learn to up my art journaling game 🙌 All thanks to you @ricki_ticki_tavy 

If you are craving some summer creative time you can still pop into Fodder School 2 @fodder.school and have a whole year of content right at your fingertips…( and you can join me as I am the September instructor;)

For all of you Paper Lovers out there…

Got a little sidetracked as another idea popped into my head -> from Master sheet to Zine...MasterZines.

Ok. Ok. Back to regularly scheduled programming, but I bet you are intrigued..

( thanks @ricki_ticki_tavy for getting all the creative ideas flowing)

A little bit of Summer.. A little bit of Fall. A new season is upon us. 

My favorite time of the year and I am starting it off the way I love as the September teacher for Fodder School 2. Class begins today! 

I am excited to share all  that I know and I am also excited to be right there  beside you, as a student, taking my own class. It’s all about discovery and trying new things so prepare to make a whole lot of marks and layer a whole lot of color. 

We are in the final month of Fodder School 2, but you can still join in! You will have instant access to my class plus all the lessons right from the beginning. It’s lifetime access so you can pop in at any time for a creative fix 🎨 Link is above in my Bio

Splish..Splash..Stamp..Splatter..Sing

(And yes, another white tee shirt was harmed in the process ..)

Enjoying September #fodderschool

Thinking out loud..and definitely not to the beat😉

Quick little studies to see what lights me up  #fodderschool  Enjoy the weekend!

Mix + Match

September’s leftover collage paper bits making up my August Scrap journal. Nothing goes to waste around here ✂️ and nothing makes me happier than that perfect paper piece  finding its place.

August + September #fodderschoolproject

September Fodder School #fodderschoolproject

A very big Thank you to Fodder School for allowing me to share my love of all things collage💫What an Abundance of love, enthusiasm, inspiration  and support. It’s everything community is suppose to be and such a nice reminder of its importance in all things. Thank you for showing me your ways.

For those that want more and are excited to move forwards -> Fodder School 3 starts tomorrow! Another year of all the mixed media techniques coming together to create something beautiful. Pop on over to @fodder.school to join in!

Lost in transition..

Taking some time off to refuel and recharge. Travel + family time, filling the heart and the head for the winter months ahead. I appreciate my art breaks, but I always feel like a part of me is missing. It definitely puts me in a mood 🫤

Starting today  it’s full steam ahead -> Paper. Paint. Pattern. Big. Small. Messy. Neat. Sewn. All the ways, any which way 🎨 ✂️

Right side brain is in full mark making mode. Left side brain is wondering why we can’t just do what we always do -> cut it all up and call it collage.

Working on my loosey goosey, non dominant hand, stand on my head kind of free flowing marks. Thriving a bit of imperfect. It’s not easy, that’s for sure..

The most art fun I have had in a while.

Some pops of color for you as the days get shorter and life shifts into all the shades of gray.

Following my curiosity with these larger works. New color palettes and finding shapes in and amongst all the layers of paint. .so many layers. My daily dose of color keeping me happy and content. 

I hope you are enjoying all the holiday hoopla💫

In my creative world this week:

Intention: starting with an intention. Feels like…winter

Inspiration: from old work-> new work

Idea making: thoughts about trees

Imagination: sketchbook wanderings 

Intuition: marks that feel just right to me

Newsletter 🎨 Please sign up above for more info on upcoming classes( online and in person), available work and mindful musings about the creative process. Link is above in profile 💛Enjoy the weekend!

2024 -> Start each day with a Happy Thought. Inspire and interact. Collaborate.

My creative year brings you a little bit of everything🎨Morning pages - Art Journals - Paper piles - Wall art…A big Yes to all of it! 

Thank you so much for following along my creative path with me. I love the collaborations, the connection + the community we have formed here. I am always amazed at the creative ways we express ourselves. Thank you for showing up and showing it all off. You inspire me💫

Wishing you a wonderful 2024!

I like stick trees..

I live in and amongst the  forest. I walk in it daily. I observe and often collect findings from within. It is where some of my best thoughts and ideas come from. The feeling of being within the forest often shows up in my work, the colors, texture and movement, but when it actually comes to painting these trees…

Stick trees…There is just something about them that makes me happy.

CREATIVE INSIGHT

All of my favorite work is a result of mistakes well made along the way. Always thankful for my sketchbook and always remain open to something new. 🎨 Paint- Cut- Paste ✂️ 

I have really enjoyed participating in Tara Levers #21daysinmyartworld The prompts have got me thinking! A great opportunity to start the new year by reflecting on yourself as an artist -> past and present… And a little bit of fun seeing what others within our community are up to💫

I have been working along and posting in my stories ( see the Highlight button to follow along) 

Hands up if you are taking the challenge too so I can pop by for a read.

A visual journey of my creative process
Licensed artist working from Whistler/Brunswick Beach B.C
